  "class": "TimeSeriesMomentum",
  "type": "momentum",
  "subtype": "trend_following",
  "description": "Each asset is evaluated purely on its own past return over a 12-month lookback window. If the trend is positive, go long; if negative, go short. Position sizes are scaled by inverse realized volatility (risk-parity weighting) so each market contributes equal risk.",
  "core_logic": "Signal = sign(return over past N months). Position size = target_vol / realized_vol. Applied across a diversified portfolio of 50-200 futures markets.",
